New Patient Portal Coming May 2
CommonSpirit Patient Portal, powered by MyChart, will replace MyVirginiaMas=
on
=20
Dear Valued Patient,
We are writing to share an important update with you. Virginia Mason Franci=
scan Health (VMFH), including Virginia Mason Medical Center, is a member of=
 CommonSpirit Health, a national health system caring for patients and supp=
orting healthier communities across the country.=20

Together, we are launching the CommonSpirit Patient Portal and Mobile App s=
o you can continue to access your health information and manage your care.

While the MyVirginiaMason portal you use to access your health information =
online is changing, your care is not. You will continue to receive care fro=
m the same trusted providers.
=20
Key dates
=20
-On April 17, online scheduling will no longer be available through MyVirgi=
niaMason. If you need to schedule or change an appointment between April 17=
 and May 2, please call your clinic or facility.
-On April 29, MyVirginiaMason will become read-only. This means patient/pro=
vider messaging will not be available through MyVirginiaMason. However, you=
 will still be able to view your historical health information. If you need=
 to contact your provider during this time, please call your clinic.
-On May 2, you will begin using the CommonSpirit Patient Portal, powered by=
 MyChart, to access and manage your health information going forward.
=20
Next steps
=20
You do not need to do anything right now.=20

On May 2, you can find clear instructions on how to download the app and cr=
eate an account on our website <https://engage.commonspirit.org/OTM4LUhESC0=
1NTIAAAGhB1aWU5XP4IqgwNvO1JzR5_P497hvJ0rNbWUGIdfHr3Ee8ebVv3mRecG0hbGAOmHw3t=
Bl79g=3D>. If you already use MyChart, you=E2=80=99ll be able to easily con=
nect your MyChart accounts when the new app is available.

This change is the first step toward a unified patient portal for all locat=
ions across the Northwest.

Your health is our top priority, and we are committed to making this transi=
tion as smooth as possible. You can find more information and answers to co=
mmonly asked questions online at <https://engage.commonspirit.org/OTM4LUhES=
C01NTIAAAGhB1aWU5XP4IqgwNvO1JzR5_P497hvJ0rNbWUGIdfHr3Ee8ebVv3mRecG0hbGAOmHw=
3tBl79g=3D>. =20

Thank you for trusting us with your care.=20

Sincerely,=20
Virginia Mason Franciscan Health


Please do not reply to this email address, it is for outbound communication=
